<title>USA: Ford Motor sells $500 million in century bonds.</title>
<headline>Ford Motor sells $500 million in century bonds.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>The following 100-year bond</p>
<p>issue from Ford Motor Co was priced on Thursday, according to</p>
<p>lead manager Bear Stearns &amp; Co Inc.</p>
<p>BORROWER FORD MOTOR CO</p>
<p>AMT $500 MLN	 COUPON 7.70 PCT   MATURITY 5/15/2097</p>
<p>TYPE BONDS	   ISS PRICE 98.591  FIRST PAY DATE 11/1/97</p>
<p>LAST MOODY'S A1    YIELD 7.81 PCT    PAY FREQ SEMI-ANNUAL</p>
<p>LAST S&amp;P A-PLUS    SPREAD +85 BPS    CALLABLE NON-CALLABLE</p>
<p>((--U.S. Corporate Bond Unit, 212 859-1662))</p>
